    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 10A: CCK-4 (1.5um) enhanced the K+-stimulated [3H]GABA release as compared to control in amygdala slices.\nFigure 10B: This effect on GABA release was fully prevented by the addition of a selective CCK-2 antagonist, CR2945.\n\nFigure 11: Bathing the amygdala slices with DNQX, a glutamatergic AMPA/kainic receptor antagonist blocked the CCK-4 facilitated effect on GABA release. This indicates that CCK-4 induced facilitation of [3H]GABA is dependent on AMPA/kainate glutamatergic receptors.\n\nThe [3H]GABA release was measured as described in Pérez de la Mora et al .,1993.\n\n11/01/2021 Dnyanada: The paper demonstrates the role of neuropeptide CCK4 in modulating GABA release in the amygdala.\nThe Uniprot ID was selected for Cholecystokinin (taxonomy: rat). However, it must be noted that the effect on GABA release was only produced by CCK4 and not its isoforms.. Experimental description: Male Wistar rats were used for measuring the effect of CCK on [3H]GABA release in amygdalar slices.",
